translate ru strings:

    old "With the Shah and his advisors retreating to the war room, princess Samayra was left to herself by the dais."
    new "With the Shah and his advisors retreating to the war room, princess Samayra was left to herself by the dais."

    old "Sarah strode across the room and stopped near the steps of the throne."
    new "Sarah strode across the room and stopped near the steps of the throne."

    old "She'd have to try, if only to tell Xan that she did."
    new "She'd have to try, if only to tell Xan that she did."

    old "The girl seemed almost startled at being addressed so directly."
    new "The girl seemed almost startled at being addressed so directly."

    old "Ooh, uhm, hello?"
    new "Ooh, uhm, hello?"

    old "My name's Sarah."
    new "My name's Sarah."

    old "It remained quiet."
    new "It remained quiet."

    old "You're Samayra, right?"
    new "You're Samayra, right?"

    old "I was just here, with the mage, I heard your father mention your name."
    new "I was just here, with the mage, I heard your father mention your name."

    old "Ooh, I'm sorry, I didn't pay much attention."
    new "Ooh, I'm sorry, I didn't pay much attention."

    old "If you're looking for my father, he's gone off to his war room."
    new "If you're looking for my father, he's gone off to his war room."

    old "Sarah tried to make eye contact, but the girl mostly looked to the floor."
    new "Sarah tried to make eye contact, but the girl mostly looked to the floor."

    old "That's fine, I was really hoping to talk to you."
    new "That's fine, I was really hoping to talk to you."

    old "She looked up in sudden surprise."
    new "She looked up in sudden surprise."

    old "Me? Why would you want to talk to me?"
    new "Me? Why would you want to talk to me?"

    old "Yeah. I've never been to Bagrad palace before, and I was just feeling, I don't know, lonely?"
    new "Yeah. I've never been to Bagrad palace before, and I was just feeling, I don't know, lonely?"

    old "Sarah saw smile creep across Samayra's face, as though she recognized what Sarah was saying."
    new "Sarah saw smile creep across Samayra's face, as though she recognized what Sarah was saying."

    old "Yes, it can be a lonely place."
    new "Yes, it can be a lonely place."

    old "The rooms haven't been prepared yet, and I keep getting lost in these hallways. I was hoping maybe you could show me around?"
    new "The rooms haven't been prepared yet, and I keep getting lost in these hallways. I was hoping maybe you could show me around?"

    old "Uhm...I could ask one of the servants, maybe..."
    new "Uhm...I could ask one of the servants, maybe..."

    old "But I'd like it to be you."
    new "But I'd like it to be you."

    old "Sarah watched the girl look around, but there was nobody to tell her how to respond."
    new "Sarah watched the girl look around, but there was nobody to tell her how to respond."

    old "Ooh...sure, yes, I could do that, I know every spot in the palace. Where do you want to go?"
    new "Ooh...sure, yes, I could do that, I know every spot in the palace. Where do you want to go?"

    old "The palace was build like a tomb. Endless stone slabs and few windows to be found. She wanted to see the sky."
    new "The palace was build like a tomb. Endless stone slabs and few windows to be found. She wanted to see the sky."

    old "The gardens, perhaps? I heard they're beautiful."
    new "The gardens, perhaps? I heard they're beautiful."

    old "Sarah watched Samayra's face light up."
    new "Sarah watched Samayra's face light up."

    old "They are! Here, follow me and I'll take you there."
    new "They are! Here, follow me and I'll take you there."

    old "Sarah felt Samayra grab her hand. She began to pull her along. The timid girl seemed to have vanished for a moment."
    new "Sarah felt Samayra grab her hand. She began to pull her along. The timid girl seemed to have vanished for a moment."

    old "The gardens of Bagrad palace are really famous. We use special airducts and waterways to create specific environments for the plants to thrive in."
    new "The gardens of Bagrad palace are really famous. We use special airducts and waterways to create specific environments for the plants to thrive in."

    old "The goal is to mimic the plant's natural environment."
    new "The goal is to mimic the plant's natural environment."

    old "You'll see plants here that don't grow anywhere else in the world."
    new "You'll see plants here that don't grow anywhere else in the world."

    old "Sarah walked along with Samayra through the great hallways of the palace."
    new "Sarah walked along with Samayra through the great hallways of the palace."

    old "Where before the presence of servants had been sparse, here the palace seemed nearly deserted, except for the occasional guard patrol."
    new "Where before the presence of servants had been sparse, here the palace seemed nearly deserted, except for the occasional guard patrol."

    old "Torches mounted on the walls kept the hallway illuminated, but so vast was the palace that the torches didn't so much bring light as seem to struggle to hold the darkness off."
    new "Torches mounted on the walls kept the hallway illuminated, but so vast was the palace that the torches didn't so much bring light as seem to struggle to hold the darkness off."

    old "We don't get many visitors, so it's always nice when I get a chance to show them off."
    new "We don't get many visitors, so it's always nice when I get a chance to show them off."

    old "Otherwise it's mostly just me and father who get to appreciate them."
    new "Otherwise it's mostly just me and father who get to appreciate them."

    old "It seemed strang to Sarah. Castle Reinmeer had always buzzed with and endless coming-and-going of nobles from all over Rosanna and its neighbouring kingdoms."
    new "It seemed strang to Sarah. Castle Reinmeer had always buzzed with and endless coming-and-going of nobles from all over Rosanna and its neighbouring kingdoms."

    old "Doesn't anyone visit?"
    new "Doesn't anyone visit?"

    old "Ooh, they do, sometimes, but it's not like it used to be. Father told me that when he was young there used to be visitors every day, but they've stopped coming. Now we maybe get visitors every month."
    new "Ooh, they do, sometimes, but it's not like it used to be. Father told me that when he was young there used to be visitors every day, but they've stopped coming. Now we maybe get visitors every month."

    old "It was the slow tragedy of an empire that did not fall in one day, but instead, seemed to have been falling for centuries."
    new "It was the slow tragedy of an empire that did not fall in one day, but instead, seemed to have been falling for centuries."

    old "A gradual yet ongoing collapse."
    new "A gradual yet ongoing collapse."

    old "One day, Sarah realized, there might be nobody left in the city."
    new "One day, Sarah realized, there might be nobody left in the city."

    old "Just monuments, great works that the people of the world no longer cared or had need for."
    new "Just monuments, great works that the people of the world no longer cared or had need for."

    old "You said earlier that the palace can be a lonely place. Are you?"
    new "You said earlier that the palace can be a lonely place. Are you?"

    old "Am I what?"
    new "Am I what?"

    old "Lonely."
    new "Lonely."

    old "The girl fiddled with her thumbs as they walked."
    new "The girl fiddled with her thumbs as they walked."

    old "Maybe, sometimes. But I'm the princess of Bagrad. Our family stands apart from everyone else. We're meant to be alone."
    new "Maybe, sometimes. But I'm the princess of Bagrad. Our family stands apart from everyone else. We're meant to be alone."

    old "Sarah listened, but Samayra didn't seem very convinced of the words she was saying."
    new "Sarah listened, but Samayra didn't seem very convinced of the words she was saying."

    old "Did your father tell you that?"
    new "Did your father tell you that?"

    old "She looked up in surprise."
    new "She looked up in surprise."

    old "It didn't really sound like you believed it yourself."
    new "It didn't really sound like you believed it yourself."

    old "Maybe, I don't know..."
    new "Maybe, I don't know..."

    old "Father tells me a lot of things, and I try to listen. He knows a lot about a lot."
    new "Father tells me a lot of things, and I try to listen. He knows a lot about a lot."

    old "I'm sure you're educated, right?"
    new "I'm sure you're educated, right?"

    old "I am, of course, but it's different. My father has seen so much of the world, and I've never even left the palace."
    new "I am, of course, but it's different. My father has seen so much of the world, and I've never even left the palace."

    old "The confession struck Sarah."
    new "The confession struck Sarah."

    old "The idea of this girl, so nearly her own age, and yet trapped in this palace for an entire lifetime."
    new "The idea of this girl, so nearly her own age, and yet trapped in this palace for an entire lifetime."

    old "It seemed cruel to her."
    new "It seemed cruel to her."

    old "You've never left?"
    new "You've never left?"

    old "Never. Everything I need is in here, and everything that isn't can be brought to me. Why should I ever leave?"
    new "Never. Everything I need is in here, and everything that isn't can be brought to me. Why should I ever leave?"

    old "It was a cage. A comfortable one, but a cage all the same."
    new "It was a cage. A comfortable one, but a cage all the same."

    old "Don't you want to see the world?"
    new "Don't you want to see the world?"

    old "Maybe. I've tried talking to father about it, but he won't listen. He says it's much too dangerous."
    new "Maybe. I've tried talking to father about it, but he won't listen. He says it's much too dangerous."

    old "But who knows, look where we are now..."
    new "But who knows, look where we are now..."

    old "An army of outsiders is camped outside of our gates."
    new "An army of outsiders is camped outside of our gates."

    old "The girl suddenly laughed. It was the kind of laugh that was meant to cover up pain."
    new "The girl suddenly laughed. It was the kind of laugh that was meant to cover up pain."

    old "I've spend all my life hiding here to stay safe from the outside world, and now the outside world has come to my doorstep."
    new "I've spend all my life hiding here to stay safe from the outside world, and now the outside world has come to my doorstep."

    old "Samayra suddenly stopped. Her shoulders began to shake, a soft sob escaped her mouth."
    new "Samayra suddenly stopped. Her shoulders began to shake, a soft sob escaped her mouth."

    old "Please, you're a mage, you have incredible power..."
    new "Please, you're a mage, you have incredible power..."

    old "Will you keep me and my father safe if the army...if they get inside the city?"
    new "Will you keep me and my father safe if the army...if they get inside the city?"

    old "Sarah placed one hand on Samayra and kept it there until her sobbing slowly ebbed."
    new "Sarah placed one hand on Samayra and kept it there until her sobbing slowly ebbed."

    old "With her other hand, she grabbed Samayra's face and lifted it up, forcing her to meet her eyes."
    new "With her other hand, she grabbed Samayra's face and lifted it up, forcing her to meet her eyes."

    old "I promise you, I'll do everything in my power to protect your family."
    new "I promise you, I'll do everything in my power to protect your family."

    old "A genuine smile crept over Samayra's face."
    new "A genuine smile crept over Samayra's face."

    old "The two began to walk again and soon found themselves in the gardens of the palace."
    new "The two began to walk again and soon found themselves in the gardens of the palace."

    old "It was stunning."
    new "It was stunning."

    old "Sarah had seen much in her life, especially since she had met Xan, but this place was utterly unique."
    new "Sarah had seen much in her life, especially since she had met Xan, but this place was utterly unique."

    old "Trees, bushes and flowers of seemingly endless variations, stood spread out over a great space."
    new "Trees, bushes and flowers of seemingly endless variations, stood spread out over a great space."

    old "Above them, the dark night was undone by the countless stars in heaven, which seemed to Sarah to shine brighter here than anywhere else."
    new "Above them, the dark night was undone by the countless stars in heaven, which seemed to Sarah to shine brighter here than anywhere else."

    old "Even in the dark, the many colours and shapes of the plants nearly overwhelmed the senses."
    new "Even in the dark, the many colours and shapes of the plants nearly overwhelmed the senses."

    old "As the two walked into the garden and the plants began to surround them in every direction, Sarah could almost believe she wasn't in the palace anymore."
    new "As the two walked into the garden and the plants began to surround them in every direction, Sarah could almost believe she wasn't in the palace anymore."

    old "Samayra turned to Sarah as they walked through the garden."
    new "Samayra turned to Sarah as they walked through the garden."

    old "This is my favorite place in the entire palace."
    new "This is my favorite place in the entire palace."

    old "When I'm here, I can almost kind of imagine what the world outside must look like."
    new "When I'm here, I can almost kind of imagine what the world outside must look like."

    old "I get that, but I've been all over the world, and I've never seen a place like this before."
    new "I get that, but I've been all over the world, and I've never seen a place like this before."

    old "Samayra grabbed Sarah's hand and began to guide her again."
    new "Samayra grabbed Sarah's hand and began to guide her again."

    old "Here, follow me!"
    new "Here, follow me!"

    old "There was an excitement to her that overpowered her otherwise demure nature."
    new "There was an excitement to her that overpowered her otherwise demure nature."

    old "Sarah let herself be guided, weaving in between the plants, going deeper and deeper into the garden, which by now was thick as jungle."
    new "Sarah let herself be guided, weaving in between the plants, going deeper and deeper into the garden, which by now was thick as jungle."

    old "After a brief few minutes, they reached a clearing near the center. A small bench sat out under an arbor, covered in an exotic plant that Sarah had never seen before."
    new "After a brief few minutes, they reached a clearing near the center. A small bench sat out under an arbor, covered in an exotic plant that Sarah had never seen before."

    old "Samayra sat down on the bench and motioned for Sarah to join her, which she did."
    new "Samayra sat down on the bench and motioned for Sarah to join her, which she did."

    old "This is where I go when I want to be alone. It's so hidden, I don't think even my father knows about it."
    new "This is where I go when I want to be alone. It's so hidden, I don't think even my father knows about it."

    old "Sarah looked around the clearing. Near the edges, plants of all kinds grew so thick they blocked any view in or out."
    new "Sarah looked around the clearing. Near the edges, plants of all kinds grew so thick they blocked any view in or out."

    old "She turned towards Samayra, who she found eagerly staring at her."
    new "She turned towards Samayra, who she found eagerly staring at her."

    old "You're so pretty."
    new "You're so pretty."

    old "To her own surprise, Sarah found herself embarassed at the compliment."
    new "To her own surprise, Sarah found herself embarassed at the compliment."

    old "Sarah said the words half laughing."
    new "Sarah said the words half laughing."

    old "Ooh, sorry..."
    new "Ooh, sorry..."

    old "I mean, we don't get a lot of people here who look like you. Your blonde hair, I just, I meant..."
    new "I mean, we don't get a lot of people here who look like you. Your blonde hair, I just, I meant..."

    old "I'm sorry, I'm rambling, I don't know why I said that."
    new "I'm sorry, I'm rambling, I don't know why I said that."

    old "It's ok. You're very pretty too."
    new "It's ok. You're very pretty too."

    old "Samayra smiled at her compliment."
    new "Samayra smiled at her compliment."

    old "Where are you from, anyway?"
    new "Where are you from, anyway?"

    old "I live in Lethram now, but I was born in Rosanna."
    new "I live in Lethram now, but I was born in Rosanna."

    old "Mentioning the word caused a sadness to come over Samayra's face."
    new "Mentioning the word caused a sadness to come over Samayra's face."

    old "Sarah realized she should have known better."
    new "Sarah realized she should have known better."

    old "It had been like this ever since the fall of Rosanna to the eastern tribesmen. Everywhere you went, mentioning Rosanna would invite stares of pity."
    new "It had been like this ever since the fall of Rosanna to the eastern tribesmen. Everywhere you went, mentioning Rosanna would invite stares of pity."

    old "Rosanna's people had become either refugees if they were lucky, or slaves to the tribesmen. A pitied people, everywhere they went."
    new "Rosanna's people had become either refugees if they were lucky, or slaves to the tribesmen. A pitied people, everywhere they went."

    old "I'm so sorry for you, I heard about what happened there. It's horrible."
    new "I'm so sorry for you, I heard about what happened there. It's horrible."

    old "Sarah waved her hand, hoping to dismiss the topic."
    new "Sarah waved her hand, hoping to dismiss the topic."

    old "Don't worry. It's been many years, I've managed to move on."
    new "Don't worry. It's been many years, I've managed to move on."

    old "To Sarah's surprise, Samayra did not let it go. Sarah nearly physically jolted when she felt Samayra embrace her."
    new "To Sarah's surprise, Samayra did not let it go. Sarah nearly physically jolted when she felt Samayra embrace her."

    old "Sarah began to softly sob."
    new "Sarah began to softly sob."

    old "Why did this still hurt her so?"
    new "Why did this still hurt her so?"

    old "Why was she still so weak that even a kind hug could cause her to breakdown."
    new "Why was she still so weak that even a kind hug could cause her to breakdown."

    old "Maybe it had been years since someone had shown her a simple kindness like this, and with ease, Sarah felt her walls break."
    new "Maybe it had been years since someone had shown her a simple kindness like this, and with ease, Sarah felt her walls break."

    old "She wept, openly into Samayra's shoulders. Wordlessly, the princess of Bagrad held her."
    new "She wept, openly into Samayra's shoulders. Wordlessly, the princess of Bagrad held her."

    old "After a few minutes, Sarah managed to regain her composure, breaking free from the embrace and wiping her tears away."
    new "After a few minutes, Sarah managed to regain her composure, breaking free from the embrace and wiping her tears away."

    old "I'm sorry about that, I don't know what happened."
    new "I'm sorry about that, I don't know what happened."

    old "I cry too, sometimes."
    new "I cry too, sometimes."

    old "Sometimes father would go on far away visits, and I would be here all alone, and it just felt so lonely."
    new "Sometimes father would go on far away visits, and I would be here all alone, and it just felt so lonely."

    old "I would just come here and cry till I felt better."
    new "I would just come here and cry till I felt better."

    old "I think it helps, in a way, you know? Letting all the emotions out so they don't stay inside of you."
    new "I think it helps, in a way, you know? Letting all the emotions out so they don't stay inside of you."

    old "Yeah, maybe that's true. It's been a long time since I cried like that though."
    new "Yeah, maybe that's true. It's been a long time since I cried like that though."

    old "Samayra smiled back at her."
    new "Samayra smiled back at her."

    old "Well, if you get too sad, it's easy. You just have to throw all the emotions out."
    new "Well, if you get too sad, it's easy. You just have to throw all the emotions out."

    old "Sarah gave Samayra a confused look."
    new "Sarah gave Samayra a confused look."

    old "Throw them out?"
    new "Throw them out?"

    old "Yeah, like this!"
    new "Yeah, like this!"

    old "Suddenly, Samayra leapt off the bench and landed perfectly balanced on one foot."
    new "Suddenly, Samayra leapt off the bench and landed perfectly balanced on one foot."

    old "For as small and lithe as she was, Samayra excercised a great strength from the tip of her toes, spinning her body around on one foot."
    new "For as small and lithe as she was, Samayra excercised a great strength from the tip of her toes, spinning her body around on one foot."

    old "As she spun she turned her body into the movement, placing down her other foot."
    new "As she spun she turned her body into the movement, placing down her other foot."

    old "Her body effortlessly followed the movements of her legs. Gracefully and with ease she made her body flow like water."
    new "Her body effortlessly followed the movements of her legs. Gracefully and with ease she made her body flow like water."

    old "Each step followed into the next, at every moment, her body turning and turning, her hair wildly flailing around."
    new "Each step followed into the next, at every moment, her body turning and turning, her hair wildly flailing around."

    old "There was a chaos here, but it was also obvious that Samayra excercised a control over it."
    new "There was a chaos here, but it was also obvious that Samayra excercised a control over it."

    old "Sarah was entranced by the sight."
    new "Sarah was entranced by the sight."

    old "It was not merely the beauty of Samayra, or the beauty of her performance, but Sarah could also feel an old part of herself return."
    new "It was not merely the beauty of Samayra, or the beauty of her performance, but Sarah could also feel an old part of herself return."

    old "Sarah remembered her own dancing lessons, how she had dedicated month after month to mastering the many dances that would be expected of a Rosannian princess."
    new "Sarah remembered her own dancing lessons, how she had dedicated month after month to mastering the many dances that would be expected of a Rosannian princess."

    old "She remembered how she would rush to her father, whenever she had mastered a new dance, and how she would show it to him."
    new "She remembered how she would rush to her father, whenever she had mastered a new dance, and how she would show it to him."

    old "Sarah suddenly recognized herself in Samayra in a way she had not yet before."
    new "Sarah suddenly recognized herself in Samayra in a way she had not yet before."

    old "Join and dance."
    new "Join and dance."

    old "It's not enough for Sarah to watch. From a place deep within herself, she wants to join."
    new "It's not enough for Sarah to watch. From a place deep within herself, she wants to join."

    old "Sarah gives in to the desire."
    new "Sarah gives in to the desire."

    old "She leaps off the bench, landing in th grass near Samayra."
    new "She leaps off the bench, landing in th grass near Samayra."

    old "Samayra is surprised at first, but does not break her performance."
    new "Samayra is surprised at first, but does not break her performance."

    old "Sarah draws from her own experience, her training."
    new "Sarah draws from her own experience, her training."

    old "It takes a few moments for the two to find their rhythm."
    new "It takes a few moments for the two to find their rhythm."

    old "But with each step, twirl and leap, the two slowly begin to discover the patterns of the other's movements."
    new "But with each step, twirl and leap, the two slowly begin to discover the patterns of the other's movements."

    old "Modulating, adapting, altering, the two find a matching pace."
    new "Modulating, adapting, altering, the two find a matching pace."

    old "Sarah and Samayra dance in circles, each stepping in the motion of the other, matching, responding. Each leads and follows at the same time."
    new "Sarah and Samayra dance in circles, each stepping in the motion of the other, matching, responding. Each leads and follows at the same time."

    old "Sarah spins and throws her hair around and begins to lose herself."
    new "Sarah spins and throws her hair around and begins to lose herself."

    old "For a moment, there is no magic, no duty, no war. There's only two people, each caught in a moment with the other. Life turns simple and small."
    new "For a moment, there is no magic, no duty, no war. There's only two people, each caught in a moment with the other. Life turns simple and small."

    old "Sarah turns back around and sees Samayra, standing still, breathing heavily from the exhaustion."
    new "Sarah turns back around and sees Samayra, standing still, breathing heavily from the exhaustion."

    old "She crosses the distance between them."
    new "She crosses the distance between them."

    old "Sarah wraps her arms around Samayra's waist and pulls her close."
    new "Sarah wraps her arms around Samayra's waist and pulls her close."

    old "She can feel Samayra's breasts pressing against hers."
    new "She can feel Samayra's breasts pressing against hers."

    old "This close, she can see the sudden uncertainty in Samayra's eyes."
    new "This close, she can see the sudden uncertainty in Samayra's eyes."

    old "Sarah wants her to know her. She begins to pull on Samayra's waist, guiding her, leading her, into a classic Rosannan dance."
    new "Sarah wants her to know her. She begins to pull on Samayra's waist, guiding her, leading her, into a classic Rosannan dance."

    old "The moves are new to Samayra, but she adapts quickly to the guidance of Sarah."
    new "The moves are new to Samayra, but she adapts quickly to the guidance of Sarah."

    old "Before long, the two are dancing slowly through the garden clearing, in perfect unity."
    new "Before long, the two are dancing slowly through the garden clearing, in perfect unity."

    old "Their faces are close."
    new "Their faces are close."

    old "Sarah becomes more aware as they slow down."
    new "Sarah becomes more aware as they slow down."

    old "This was a dance more meant for one's wedding than for two women."
    new "This was a dance more meant for one's wedding than for two women."

    old "And yet she doesn't break, nor does Samayra."
    new "And yet she doesn't break, nor does Samayra."

    old "She can feel her breath upon her face. Is she aware of mine, Sarah wonders."
    new "She can feel her breath upon her face. Is she aware of mine, Sarah wonders."

    old "Sarah kisses her."
    new "Sarah kisses her."

    old "She can feel Samayra's stunned reaction, her body suddenly tense, but it gives way to surrender as Samayra's mouth opens and her tongue meets hers."
    new "She can feel Samayra's stunned reaction, her body suddenly tense, but it gives way to surrender as Samayra's mouth opens and her tongue meets hers."

    old "What am I doing, Sarah thinks."
    new "What am I doing, Sarah thinks."

    old "But her reason is powerless here. From a far more primal place, she wants to hold Samayra, hold every part of her."
    new "But her reason is powerless here. From a far more primal place, she wants to hold Samayra, hold every part of her."

    old "Suddenly, she can feel Samayra break their kiss."
    new "Suddenly, she can feel Samayra break their kiss."

    old "Their eyes meet again, and for a moment, neither speaks."
    new "Their eyes meet again, and for a moment, neither speaks."

    old "The question seems genuine."
    new "The question seems genuine."

    old "Did you not want me to?"
    new "Did you not want me to?"

    old "Sarah can see Samayra is afraid to answer."
    new "Sarah can see Samayra is afraid to answer."

    old "Instead, Samayra answers without words, leaning back in and kissing Sarah."
    new "Instead, Samayra answers without words, leaning back in and kissing Sarah."

    old "Under the stars, hidden in the garden, the two fall into each other."
    new "Under the stars, hidden in the garden, the two fall into each other."

    old "After some time has passed, the two finally break from one another."
    new "After some time has passed, the two finally break from one another."

    old "In their eyes, each can see a longing for more, yet each knows it can't happen here."
    new "In their eyes, each can see a longing for more, yet each knows it can't happen here."

    old "The council will end soon...I'll be expected..."
    new "The council will end soon...I'll be expected..."

    old "Sarah turned away, staring out into the brush."
    new "Sarah turned away, staring out into the brush."

    old "Of course, I don't know what I was thinking. We should go back inside."
    new "Of course, I don't know what I was thinking. We should go back inside."

    old "Samayra is the first walk away, grabbing Sarah's hands and pulling her along."
    new "Samayra is the first walk away, grabbing Sarah's hands and pulling her along."

    old "She gives Sarah one last kiss, before guiding her by the hand back into the palace."
    new "She gives Sarah one last kiss, before guiding her by the hand back into the palace."

    old "Neither speaks of what transpired as they walk the hallways of the palace, but it lingers in the silence between them."
    new "Neither speaks of what transpired as they walk the hallways of the palace, but it lingers in the silence between them."

    old "Sit still and observe"
